.TH "mma9551_update_config_bits" 9 "mma9551_update_config_bits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mma9551_update_config_bits \- update bits in register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mma9551_update_config_bits
.BI "(struct i2c_client *client "  ","
.BI "u8 app_id "  ","
.BI "u16 reg "  ","
.BI "u8 mask "  ","
.BI "u8 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
I2C client
.IP "app_id" 12
Application ID
.IP "reg" 12
Application register
.IP "mask" 12
Mask for the bits to update
.IP "val" 12
Value of the bits to update
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update bits in the given register using a bit mask.

Locking note: This function must be called with the device lock held.
Locking is not handled inside the function. Callers should ensure they
serialize access to the HW.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative value on failure.
